  "title": "Architectural Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>-To develop a schedule program for the commencement and completion of all architectural works to tie in with master schedule.</p><p>-To coordinate monitor and control Architectural subcontractor’s progress and quality of work.</p><p>-To delegate work to the general workers/supervisors and ensure it is in compliance with company/authority standards.</p><p>-Liaise with suppliers on items needed for the project and plan the delivery schedule.</p><p>-Ensure timely delivery of goods and material to site.</p><p>-Submission to consultants for materials, shop drawings and method statement approval before commencement of work.</p><p>-Arrange for architectural trade demonstration for consultant’s approval.</p><p>-Arrange for testing of architectural materials.</p><p>-Liaise with consultants to resolve technical and detailing issues for architectural work.</p><p>-Attend project coordination meetings.</p><p>-Report to Project Manager the progress of architectural work.</p><p>-Assist Project Manager in compilation of handling over documents including as-built drawings.</p><p>-Execute control measures on material/plant and equipment/utilities usage.</p><p>-Understand specifications, drawings, scope and sequence of work.</p><p>-Ability to propose alternative material/work method for architectural work.</p><p>-Ability to interpret construction drawings for any discrepancies.</p>",
